title: FONTANA: Speeding truck crashes off I-210 into car dealership
text:
By RICHARD BROOKS / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 15, 2015 Updated: 10:21 p.m. FONTANA: Speeding truck crashes off I-210 into car dealership Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article » A speeding pickup truck crashed into a car along a Fontana freeway, tumbled into a Honda dealership and damaged several additional vehicles, say California Highway Patrol officers.
The wreck was reported at 6:54 a.m. Wednesday, Oct. 14, along the eastbound lanes of I-210 west of Sierra Avenue.
The 2008 Ford F150 truck was driven by 58-year-old David Garcia of the Alta Loma� section of Rancho Cuamonga, Officer Jesus Garcia said in a written statement.
The wreck began with the F150 hitting a 1998 Ford Mustang, then veering off the freeway, flying over an embankment, crashing through a fence and into the back lot of Rock Honda Auto Dealership, according to the statement.
Garcia was taken to Arrowhead Regional Medical Center in Colton for treatment of what the CHP described as minor injuries. No one else was hurt.
Anyone with additional information may call Rancho Cucamonga-based CHP officers at 9099-980-3994.
